THE University of the Witwatersrand has confirmed its fee increase will be limited to an average of 8% for the 2017 academic year.Tuition and residence fees will increase by 8% which also applies to international students, the institution said.&ldquo;The only exception is for postgraduate programmes run in the Wits School of Governance, where tuition fees will increase by 9,5%. These increases are in line with the recommendations made by the state in September this year,&rdquo; a statement reads.In September, Minister of Higher Education and Training Blade Nzimande announced that university fees may not exceed an 8% increase in response to mass student protests against fees.Nzimande also promised that households which are earning less than R600 000 a year would not be exposed to university fee increases. &ndash; NEWS24